definition.value: Sexual attraction between two or more people of the same gender or the same gender-area (for example, a man being attracted to a transmasculine person), especially between two men.
Sexually attracted to a person defined as being of the "opposite" sex (i.e. male attracted to female or female attracted to male); more broadly, attracted to a gender that is not one's own.
Sexually attracted to people regardless of gender; alternatively, sexually attracted to people of all genders or any gender.
A gender identity in question, in the process of being questioned, or otherwise being explored.

label.value: woman who has sex with men

definition.value: Female persons who engage in sexual activity with men, regardless of how they identify themselves.

label.value: man who has sex with women

definition.value: Male persons who engage in sexual activity with women, regardless of how they identify themselves.

label.value: man who has sex with transgender women

definition.value: Men who are engage in sexual activities with transgender women.
It is important to note that men who are attracted to transgender women are expressing heterosexual desires; transgender women are women by definition.

label.value: woman who has sex with transgender men

definition.value: A woman who engages in sexual activity with transgender men.
It is important to note that women who are attracted to transgender men are expressing heterosexual desires; transgender men are men by definition.

A term used primarily, but not exclusively, in the United States to describe any person who is not considered white. The term encompasses all non-white people, emphasizing common experiences of systemic racism.
Persons who are female and of color.
Persons who are male and of color.
Transgender persons employed as sex workers or otherwise engaged in sex work.
Transgender persons engaged in street prostitution and/or street sex work.
Surgical procedures performed on parts of the trunk.
Surgical procedures performed on parts of the thorax.

Any of various surgical procedures by which a transgender person's physical appearance and function of their existing sexual characteristics are altered to resemble that socially associated with their identified gender. It is part of a treatment for gender dysphoria in transgender people.
Avoid terms which include "sex change" as they are inaccurate (referring to "sex" rather than "gender" and implying a "change" rather than an affirmation of an already present gender identity).

Avoid terms which include the word "reassignment" as no reassignment is taking place (assigned sex at birth is still assigned and such procedures are in no way tied to legal reassignment) and it implies that one's gender identity is tied solely to the surgery, rather than an internal representation of self.

Use terms like "gender confirmation surgery", "gender-affirming surgery", or "gender-validating surgery" when discussing such procedures, but outside of a clinical context, allow the person to guide discussion about these processes (i.e. it is inappropriate to ask a transgender person if they've "had the surgery" or the like).
Any of various surgeries for those expressing intersex conditions or variations.
Any of a variety of surgical procedures that alter anatomical traits to provide physical traits more comfortable to the transfeminine person's gender identity and functioning.
Any of a variety of surgical procedures that alter anatomical traits to provide physical traits more comfortable to the transmasculine person's gender identity and functioning.
Any of various facial surgeries used as treatment for transfeminine persons in alleviation of gender dysphoria.
Any of various facial surgeries used as treatment for transmasculine persons in alleviation of gender dysphoria.
Any of various genital surgeries used as treatment for transmasculine persons in alleviation of gender dysphoria.
Any of various genital surgeries used as treatment for transfeminine persons in alleviation of gender dysphoria.
Differences in access to or availability of medical facilities and services.

Removal of ovotestis.
Surgery during which an ovotestis or ovotestes are excised.
Any of various genital surgeries used as treatment for transgender persons in alleviation of gender dysphoria.
Any of various chest surgeries used as treatment for transgender persons in alleviation of gender dysphoria.

Abnormal sex differentiation or congenital intersex conditions caused by abnormal levels of steroid hormones expressed by the gonads or the adrenal glands, such as in congenital adrenal hyperplasia and adrenal cortex neoplasms.

An instance of adrenogenital syndrome that is congenital.
